</emphasis>
Labium with glossae, paraglossae and 2nd segment of labial palp relatively long (
<figureCitation box="[215,283,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1859,1884]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,1831]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,179,1831]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Larvae of Indocloeon s. str. 1–3, Indocloeon (Indocloeon) secundum sp. n.: 1–2, left and right mandibles of holotype (arrow shows seta on proximal angle of left mola); 3, labium (focus on ventral side); 4–5, Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum, labium and maxilla (focus on ventral side)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839331/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Stout setae on outer side of femur non-pectinate, apically blunt (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1068,1149,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 76–81" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,181,1727]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 76–81. Larvae of Indocloeon (Hindocloeon) continentale sp. n. 76–77, tibiae of fore and hind legs; 78–79, fore and hind legs; 80, claw; 81, outer margin of femur (76–79, holotype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839363/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
). Apex of femur normally with 2 (occasionally up to 8) stout, blunt setae. Tibiae of fore, middle and hind legs normally with one stout outerapical seta (occasionally with 2 or more such setae), without other stout setae on outer margin (as in 
<figureCitation box="[1300,1428,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–14" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1264,1289]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1239]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,181,1239]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 10–14. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) secundum sp. n. (holotype). 10–11, claw; 12, two outer-apical setae on fore tibia; 13, tibia of fore leg; 14, tibia of middle leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839335/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Figs 13–14</figureCitation>
) [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" box="[203,329,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[203,329,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[335,393,513,539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(8)]. Claw with 2 rows of denticles; in each row 2–7 (usually 3–4) most distal denticles larger than others. Hind margin of tergum I either lacks denticles or with few small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1196,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
); hind margin of each tergum II–VIII bears regular row of long denticles fused at most part of their length (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1227,585,612]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Figs 16–18</figureCitation>
); denticles on posterior margin of tergum IX also fused proximally; on middle of posterior margin of tergum IX (behind submedian pair of setae) denticles shorter (
<figureCitation box="[512,597,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); denticles on posterior margin of tergum X partly fused proximally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Hind margins of sterna I–II lack denticles; each sternum III–IX with fused denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1252,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
); on sternum IX of male fused denticles located only by sides of protogonostyli and between protogonostyli (
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[1197,1334,729,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="361 - 376" refId="ref14683" refString="Kluge, N. J. (2012) Non-African representatives of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20 (4), 361 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.02" type="journal article" year="2012">Kluge 2012</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 35). Scales on abdominal terga and sterna blunt, forming irregular transverse rows (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1145,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Figs 24</figureCitation>
). Each segment of cercus with regular row of equal short denticles, without elongated denticles (
<figureCitation box="[949,1034,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,181,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1817]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 15–24. Larva of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 15–20, posterior margins of abdominal terga I, II, IV, VII, IX and X (black triangle shows median line on tergum IX); 21, abdominal tergum VI; 22, abdominal sternum III; 23, cercus; 24, scales on abdominal sternum, enlarged." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). For other characters see diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" box="[182,308,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[182,308,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[315,375,837,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
above, diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" box="[607,733,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[607,733,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[740,781,837,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[795,929,837,863]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="361 - 376" refId="ref14683" refString="Kluge, N. J. (2012) Non-African representatives of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20 (4), 361 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.02" type="journal article" year="2012">Kluge 2012</bibRefCitation>
and above) and former descriptions (Müller- Liebenau 1982; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[333,470,873,899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="361 - 376" refId="ref14683" refString="Kluge, N. J. (2012) Non-African representatives of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20 (4), 361 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.02" type="journal article" year="2012">Kluge 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,449,908,935]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Subimago and imago</emphasis>
. Described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[624,780,909,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="361 - 376" refId="ref14683" refString="Kluge, N. J. (2012) Non-African representatives of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20 (4), 361 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.02" type="journal article" year="2012">Kluge (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Statement that «pedicellus with basal half brown» is not quite correct, because only lateral and median sides of its basal half are brown (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1122,944,971]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1880,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. Imagines of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 35, antennae of female imago; 36, abdominal terga and sterna of male imago (genitals removed); 37, male imago; 38, abdominal terga and sterna of female imago; 39, female imago." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" box="[1189,1315,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1189,1315,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1322,1381,945,971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(9)]. In subimago of both sexes and in male imago cross veins colourless (
<figureCitation box="[950,1035,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1880,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. Imagines of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 35, antennae of female imago; 36, abdominal terga and sterna of male imago (genitals removed); 37, male imago; 38, abdominal terga and sterna of female imago; 39, female imago." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
), only in female imago cross veins darkened (
<figureCitation box="[270,354,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1880,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. Imagines of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 35, antennae of female imago; 36, abdominal terga and sterna of male imago (genitals removed); 37, male imago; 38, abdominal terga and sterna of female imago; 39, female imago." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
). Abdominal terga III–VI of both sexes always without median longitudinal stripe (
<figureCitation box="[1292,1424,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–39" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1880,1905]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,489,1856]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 35–39. Imagines of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 35, antennae of female imago; 36, abdominal terga and sterna of male imago (genitals removed); 37, male imago; 38, abdominal terga and sterna of female imago; 39, female imago." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Figs 36, 38</figureCitation>
). Proximal (1st+2nd) segment of gonostylus moderately widened at base; proximal 2/3 of its inner margin straight, at 2/3 length from base inner margin forms convex blunt angle (
<figureCitation box="[848,934,1089,1115]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–49" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1772,1797]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,460,1743]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,453,1747]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 46–49. Male genitals of Indocloeon s. str. 46, imaginal genitals of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) secundum sp. n. (holotype) (1+2, proximal segment of gonostylus; 3, distal segment of gonostylus; m.d, dorsal muscle of penis; m.gs, gonostylar muscle; m.gv, gonovectal muscle; m.s., median sterno-styligeral muscle); 47, their subimaginal exuviae; 48, gonostylus of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum; 49, its subimaginal exuviae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839347/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). For other characters see diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[233,292,1125,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
above, diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" box="[522,648,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato">
<emphasis box="[522,648,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[655,695,1125,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="lato">s. l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[709,843,1125,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="361 - 376" refId="ref14683" refString="Kluge, N. J. (2012) Non-African representatives of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20 (4), 361 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.02" type="journal article" year="2012">Kluge 2012</bibRefCitation>
and above) and former description (
<bibRefCitation author="Kluge, N. J." box="[1250,1388,1125,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" pagination="361 - 376" refId="ref14683" refString="Kluge, N. J. (2012) Non-African representatives of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata (Ephemeroptera: Baetidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20 (4), 361 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.02" type="journal article" year="2012">Kluge 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1295]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,253,1161,1187]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,246,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Egg</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Oval, about 
<quantity box="[395,494,1160,1187]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
length. Polar area bearing net-like relief [see 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller-Liebenau" authorityYear="1982" box="[998,1124,1161,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Indocloeon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[998,1124,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Indocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1130,1188,1161,1187]" pageId="5" pageNumber="456" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(15)] with cells small, lacking convexities on bottoms (
<figureCitation box="[521,607,1196,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1805,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,345,1780]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 50–52. Egg of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 50, general view; 51–52, enlarged areas marked by frames on Fig. 50." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839349" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839349/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
); remainder area of egg surface partly with sharply outlined cavities (see ibid.), partly smooth (
<figureCitation box="[395,526,1232,1259]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–52" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1805,1830]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,345,1780]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 50–52. Egg of Indocloeon (Indocloeon) primum. 50, general view; 51–52, enlarged areas marked by frames on Fig. 50." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3839349" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3839349/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="456">Figs 50–51</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
